        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47690",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For now i have created empty one row max ,,dual'' table in my db.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-27T10:17:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-27T10:17:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47695",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you provide a SQL dump with the structure of your tables and a larger sample of your ZF code where you create the SELECT query?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-27T13:25:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-27T13:25:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47697",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=davidfuhr",
                        "name": "davidfuhr",
                        "displayName": "David Fuhr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The \"dual\" table is specific to Oracle and MySQL supports this as well for compatibility reasons: http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/DUAL_table\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\n-- works in MySQL:\r\nSELECT NOW() FROM DUAL;\r\n\r\n-- works only if you have a table called \"dual\"\r\nSELECT NOW() FROM `DUAL`;\r\n\r\n-- works NOT in MySQL:\r\nSELECT NOW() FROM DUAL as t;\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nThe _renderFrom() method in Zend_Db_Select already uses the dummy table for oracle automatically if no from part is set:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\n        \/*\r\n         * If no table specified, use RDBMS-dependent solution\r\n         * for table-less query.  e.g. DUAL in Oracle.\r\n         *\/\r\n        if (empty($this->_parts[self::FROM])) {\r\n            $this->_parts[self::FROM] = $this->_getDummyTable();\r\n        }\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nSo i suggest you omit the FROM part when creating the select statement and everything should work fine for Oracle and MySQL as well.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=davidfuhr",
                        "name": "davidfuhr",
                        "displayName": "David Fuhr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-27T16:23:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-27T16:23:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47698",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=davidfuhr",
                        "name": "davidfuhr",
                        "displayName": "David Fuhr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oh, i just saw, that the _getDummyTable() method does actually nothing :)\r\n\r\nI assume it should contain something like:\r\n{noformat}\r\nreturn $this->_adapter->getDummyTable();\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nThe abstract db adapter should return an empty array (like _getDummyTable() currently does) and the oracle and oci adapters should return \"DUAL\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=davidfuhr",
                        "name": "davidfuhr",
                        "displayName": "David Fuhr",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-27T16:38:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-27T16:38:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47699",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I provided FROM... as new Zend_Db_Expr('dual').   What i should get needs to be:    {noformat} *sql.... FROM dual ...rest of sql*{noformat} .  If i provide:  ->from('dual')  i get  {noformat} *sql.... FROM 'dual'  ...rest of sql* witch is normal, but i want the 1st one to work. Without that strange aliacing something that is good, to something that cannot even validate.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-27T17:41:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-27T17:41:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47700",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Forgot to tell.. That sql of mine (as almost any under mysql that can use dual - would work totally ok without using from at all - but that is strangely prohibited by select class when using for example:  {noformat} $db->select()-> column (array('actual_time'=>new Zend_Db_Expr('CURRENT_TIME')));{noformat}\r\n\r\nPS: $db used everywhere is just:  _$db = $this->getAdapter();_",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-27T17:45:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-27T17:45:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48340",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed it by editing Zend\/Db\/Select.php, at line _1125_ oryginally containing \r\nbq. $tmp .= $this->_getQuotedTable($table['tableName'], $correlationName);\r\nto lines\r\n{noformat}\r\n             if ($table['tableName'] instanceof Zend_Db_Expr)\r\n                $tmp .= $this->_getQuotedTable($table['tableName']);\r\n            else\r\n                $tmp .= $this->_getQuotedTable($table['tableName'], $correlationName);\r\n{noformat}\r\nor to single line\r\n{noformat}\r\n                $tmp .= $this->_getQuotedTable($table['tableName'], ($table['tableName'] instanceof Zend_Db_Expr) ? null : $correlationName);\r\n{noformat}\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-04T18:19:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-04T18:19:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48341",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=seti",
                        "name": "seti",
                        "displayName": "Artur \u0141abudzi\u0144ski",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "And much more changes. Do anyone found better fix?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
